The co-pilot of a Portuguese airline was detained in Stuttgart after being found drunk in the cockpit just before take-off, German police and prosecutors said on Saturday (March 24). German police entered the cockpit and found the 40-year-old in a "highly intoxicated condition" on Friday evening, a statement said. ALSO READ:

